content:
To add data to the output of a Data Mapper, define formulas. Several types of Data Mapper (Extract, Transform, and Load) support formulas. When you define a formula, you map its output to the output JSON or Salesforce object field.

For details about operators and functions, see Function Reference.

If a variable name contains spaces or non-alphanumeric characters, enclose it in double quotes and precede with var: in formulas. To create a formula:

In the Data Mapper Interface page, go to the Formulas tab.
Click Add Formula.
In the Formula field, specify the desired logic.
For example, to determine the total price of items being purchased by a customer, enter SUM(Products:Price).

You can reference attributes in formulas using code preceded by @. For example:
Account:@GoldStarAccount == "On"

Map the result to the final output.

For an Extract Data Mapper, map the formula result to the output structure on the Output tab.
Use a colon (:) to delimit levels in the input and output paths in mappings.

For a Transform Data Mapper, map the formula result to the output structure on the Transforms tab.
Use a colon (:) to delimit levels in the input and output paths in mappings.

For a Load Data Mapper, for each sObject that you want to update, go to its Fields tab and map the formula result to the specific field that you want to update.
title: Using Formulas in Omnistudio Data Mappers
